bug.short_desc: NPE throws out when open the chart in attached rptdesign

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 86530 report design
Description: NPE throws out when open the chart in attached rptdesign
Build number: 2.3.0.v20080110-0800
Steps to reproduce: 1, open attached report design 2, double click the Chart
Expected result: If the chart is invalid type we should give user a proper exception or warning.
Actual result: NPE throws out
Error log: org.eclipse.birt.chart.ui.swt.wizard.data.BaseDataDefinitionComponent$1$AggregationAction.<init>(BaseDataDefinitionComponent.java:562) org.eclipse.birt.chart.ui.swt.wizard.data.BaseDataDefinitionComponent.createAggregationItem(BaseDataDefinitionComponent.java:671) org.eclipse.birt.chart.ui.swt.wizard.data.BaseDataDefinitionComponent.createArea(BaseDataDefinitionComponent.java:197) org.eclipse.birt.chart.ui.swt.wizard.data.DataDefinitionSelector.updateDataDefinition(DataDefinitionSelector.java:233) org.eclipse.birt.chart.ui.swt.wizard.data.DataDefinitionSelector.createArea(DataDefinitionSelector.java:212) org.eclipse.birt.chart.ui.swt.wizard.data.MultipleSeriesSelectorComponent.createArea(MultipleSeriesSelectorComponent.java:114)
seems a regression caused by new aggregation ui code?

(In reply to comment #1) > seems a regression caused by new aggregation ui code? >
It isn't a regression issue, the attached exception shows it is reproduced by old version. Also I tested current aggregation ui code, it still exists this issue, the reason is that the SeriesGrouping object might be null and don't be checked. I will fix it.
The NPE still occurs, reopen the bug.
Please try v20080129-0800 build to reproduce it.
Check if grouping setting in chart model is null to avoid NPE exception for some old reports. Also fixed another sharing binding error on adding Y optional expression items.
Verified in v20080131-0800 build, close the bug.
